//! OwnSome — OS competition kernel for RISC-V and LoongArch64
//!
//! Based on NighthawkOS (https://gitlab.eduxiji.net/T202518123995755-2974),
//! an async coroutine-based monolithic kernel written in Rust.
//!
//! Key improvements over the base:
//! - Scheduler syscalls (sched_setscheduler/getparam/getscheduler) from stub → full implementation
//! - Memory management: mremap with MAYMOVE/FIXED/DONTUNMAP support
//! - Threading: robust_list storage for NPTL compatibility
//! - Network: background net_poll_init, recvfrom poll fix, iperf accept deadlock fix
//! - Panic elimination: 7 kernel panics fixed (nlink, signal shift, user_ptr, ENOSYS, dentry, ext4, syscall 452)
//! - fanotify: removed unimplemented!() panics, added init flags support, ONDIR event filter
//! - Syscall additions: preadv/pwritev, getpriority/setpriority, sched_get_priority_max/min, fcntl locks, syslog read
//! - LTP stability: TFAIL significantly reduced, 0 kernel panics in full test runs
//!
//! References:
//! - RocketOS (T202510213995926-2475): sched_get_priority, robust_list, FIFO scheduler design
//! - Chronix (T202518123995568-675): mremap implementation design
//! - NoAxiom (T202510336995214-148): clean socket flag handling pattern
//!
//! License: GPL-3.0
//!
//! School: Beihang University (北京航空航天大学)

